<section sectnbr = "5E">
<servcat sctnbr = "05" scnbr = "05">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "4">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENCP70A5504007" svcinfotypenbr = "06" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Line Pressure Test
</title>
<ptxt>
This test is performed to check operating conditions of each part by measuring fluid pressure in fluid pressure line.
</ptxt>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect SUZUKI scan tool to DLC.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Select “Data list” mode on scan tool.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Drive vehicle so that CVT fluid temperature reaches normal operating temperature (60 to 80 &#176;C (140 to 176 &#176;F)). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A5504015"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Engine coolant temperature rises when revving engine in P or N range, but CVT fluid temperature does not rise in P or N range. Be sure to drive vehicle in order to raise CVT fluid temperature.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply parking brake and block wheels.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove fluid pressure check hole bolt.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Attach oil pressure gauge to fluid pressure check hole (1) in transaxle case.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Adapter (2) is not included in special tool (A). Use adapter included in special tool (C).
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
After attaching oil pressure gauge, check that no fluid leakage exists.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5E001">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09925-36310">
09925–36310
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5E002">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09915-75820">
09915–75820
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5E003">
<s-part>
(C)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09925-37811-001">
09925–37811–001
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP70A550009.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "62.639mm" ver = "01" gw = "184" gh = "161"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Depress brake pedal fully, run engine at idle and stall then check fluid pressure in D or R range.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not continue running engine at stall speed for longer than 5 seconds.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
After performing line pressure test, be sure to leave engine running at idle for longer than 1 minute before performing another line pressure test.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention2>
<spec>
<title>
CVT line pressure
</title>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "3" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "1.023in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.212in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "1.212in"/>
<thead>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
P or N range
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
R or D range
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1" valign = "middle" align = "center">
<ptxt>
At idle speed
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1" valign = "middle" align = "center">
<ptxt>
0.5 to 1.0 MPa (5.1 to 10.1 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 72.5 to 145 psi, 5 to 10 bar)
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1" valign = "middle" align = "center">
<ptxt>
0.5 to 1.0 MPa (5.1 to 10.1 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 72.5 to 145 psi, 5 to 10 bar)
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1" valign = "middle" align = "center">
<ptxt>
At stall speed (Reference)
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1" valign = "middle" align = "center">
<ptxt>
—
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1" valign = "middle" align = "center">
<ptxt>
4.8 to 5.3 MPa (48.9 to 54.0 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 696 to 768 psi, 48 to 53 bar)
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
If check result is OK, disconnect special tool and then tighten fluid pressure check hole bolt (1) to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T5E001">
<t-part>
Fluid pressure check hole bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
13
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
1.3
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
9.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
